            Dimensions =

func main() {
	pulumi.Run(func(ctx *pulumi.Context) error {

			return err

package generated_program;

import java.util.*;
import java.io.*;
import java.nio.*;
import com.pulumi.*;

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Pulumi.run(App::stack);
    }

    public static void stack(Context ctx) {
        final var instances = Output.of(InstancesFunctions.getInstance());

        final var cvmMonitorData = Output.of(MonitorFunctions.getData(GetDataArgs.builder()
            .namespace("QCE/CVM")
            .metricName("CPUUsage")
            .dimensions(GetDataDimensionArgs.builder()
                .name("InstanceId")
                .value(instances.apply(getInstanceResult -> getInstanceResult.instanceLists()[0].instanceId()))
                .build())
            .period(300)
            .startTime("2020-04-28T18:45:00+08:00")
            .endTime("2020-04-28T19:00:00+08:00")
            .build()));

        final var cosMonitorData = Output.of(MonitorFunctions.getData(GetDataArgs.builder()
            .namespace("QCE/COS")
            .metricName("InternetTraffic")
            .dimensions(            
                GetDataDimensionArgs.builder()
                    .name("appid")
                    .value("1258798060")
                    .build(),
                GetDataDimensionArgs.builder()
                    .name("bucket")
                    .value("test-1258798060")
                    .build())
            .period(300)
            .startTime("2020-04-28T18:30:00+08:00")
            .endTime("2020-04-28T19:00:00+08:00")

}

    </dt>
    <dd><p>Instance dimension value, eg: <code>ins-j0hk02zo</code> for cvm.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>
